	(14, 'K', 'Potassium', '<table>   <tr>     <th>Age</th>     <th>Male</th>     <th>Female</th>     <th>Pregnancy</th>     <th>Lactation</th>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>Birth to 6 months</td>     <td>400 mg</td>     <td>400 mg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>7–12 months</td>     <td>860 mg</td>     <td>860 mg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>1–3 years</td>     <td>2,000 mg</td>     <td>2,000 mg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>4–8 years</td>     <td>2,300 mg</td>     <td>2,300 mg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>9–13 years</td>     <td>2,500 mg</td>     <td>2,300 mg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>14–18 years</td>     <td>3,000 mg</td>     <td>2,300 mg</td>     <td>2,600 mg</td>     <td>2,500 mg</td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>19–50 years</td>     <td>3,400 mg</td>     <td>2,600 mg</td>     <td>2,900 mg</td>     <td>2,800 mg</td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>51+ years</td>     <td>3,400 mg</td>     <td>2,600 mg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr> </table>', 'Potassium is an essential mineral that plays a crucial role in the proper functioning of the human body. As an electrolyte, it is responsible for maintaining a healthy balance of fluids and electrical signals throughout the body, contributing to the regulation of various physiological processes.', 'minerals', '/images/minerals/1725024342371.webp'),
	(15, 'S', 'Sulfur', '13 mg/kg per 24h', 'Sulfur is a remarkable mineral that plays a crucial role in various aspects of human health. While it may not be as well-known as some of its counterparts, sulfur is an essential nutrient that contributes to the proper functioning of the body, supporting the maintenance of healthy skin, hair, and nails, as well as the detoxification processes.', 'minerals', '/images/minerals/1725024368504.webp'),
	(16, 'Na', 'Sodium', 'Less than 2,300 mg per day', 'Sodium is an essential mineral that plays a crucial role in the proper functioning of the human body. As a vital electrolyte, it is responsible for maintaining a healthy balance of fluids and electrical signals throughout the body, contributing to the regulation of various physiological processes.', 'minerals', '/images/minerals/1725024391285.webp'),
	(17, 'Cl', 'Chloride', 'Less than 2,300 mg per day', 'Chloride is an essential mineral that often goes unnoticed, but it plays a crucial role in the proper functioning of the human body. As an electrolyte, it works in tandem with other minerals like sodium and potassium to maintain a healthy balance of fluids and electrical signals throughout the body.', 'minerals', '/images/minerals/1725024419748.webp'),
	(18, 'Fe', 'Iron', '<table>   <tr>     <th>Age</th>     <th>Male</th>     <th>Female</th>     <th>Pregnancy</th>     <th>Lactation</th>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>Birth to 6 months</td>     <td>0.27 mg*</td>     <td>0.27 mg*</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>7–12 months</td>     <td>11 mg</td>     <td>11 mg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>1–3 years</td>     <td>7 mg</td>     <td>7 mg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>4–8 years</td>     <td>10 mg</td>     <td>10 mg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>9–13 years</td>     <td>8 mg</td>     <td>8 mg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>14–18 years</td>     <td>11 mg</td>     <td>15 mg</td>     <td>27 mg</td>     <td>10 mg</td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>19–50 years</td>     <td>8 mg</td>     <td>18 mg</td>     <td>27 mg</td>     <td>9 mg</td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>51+ years</td>     <td>8 mg</td>     <td>8 mg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr> </table>', 'nullaIron is an essential mineral that plays a crucial role in the proper functioning of the human body. It is a key component of hemoglobin, the protein in red blood cells responsible for transporting oxygen throughout the body, making it vital for maintaining healthy blood and supporting overall energy levels.', 'minerals', '/images/minerals/1725024441110.webp'),
	(19, 'Se', 'Selenium', '<table>   <tr>     <th>Age</th>     <th>Male</th>     <th>Female</th>     <th>Pregnancy</th>     <th>Lactation</th>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>Birth to 6 months</td>     <td>15 mcg*</td>     <td>15 mcg*</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>7–12 months</td>     <td>20 mcg*</td>     <td>20 mcg*</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>1–3 years</td>     <td>20 mcg</td>     <td>20 mcg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>4–8 years</td>     <td>30 mcg</td>     <td>30 mcg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>9–13 years</td>     <td>40 mcg</td>     <td>40 mcg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>14–18 years</td>     <td>55 mcg</td>     <td>55 mcg</td>     <td>60 mcg</td>     <td>70 mcg</td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>19–50 years</td>     <td>55 mcg</td>     <td>55 mcg</td>     <td>60 mcg</td>     <td>70 mcg</td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>51+ years</td>     <td>55 mcg</td>     <td>55 mcg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr> </table>', 'Selenium is a trace mineral that plays a crucial role in the proper functioning of the human body. While it may not be as well-known as some of its counterparts, selenium is an essential nutrient that contributes to the maintenance of a healthy immune system and the prevention of various chronic diseases.', 'minerals', '/images/minerals/1725024477397.webp'),
