	(22, 'Cr', 'Chromium', '<table>   <tr>     <th>Age</th>     <th>Male</th>     <th>Female</th>     <th>Pregnancy</th>     <th>Lactation</th>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>Birth to 6 months*</td>     <td>0.2 mcg</td>     <td>0.2 mcg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>7–12 months*</td>     <td>5.5 mcg</td>     <td>5.5 mcg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>1–3 years</td>     <td>11 mcg</td>     <td>11 mcg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>4–8 years</td>     <td>15 mcg</td>     <td>15 mcg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>9–13 years</td>     <td>25 mcg</td>     <td>21 mcg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>14–18 years</td>     <td>35 mcg</td>     <td>24 mcg</td>     <td>29 mcg</td>     <td>44 mcg</td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>19–50 years</td>     <td>35 mcg</td>     <td>25 mcg</td>     <td>30 mcg</td>     <td>45 mcg</td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>51+ years</td>     <td>30 mcg</td>     <td>20 mcg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr> </table>', 'Chromium is an essential trace mineral that plays a vital role in the regulation of blood sugar levels. While it may not be as well-known as some of its counterparts, chromium is a crucial nutrient that contributes to the proper functioning of the body\'s insulin and glucose metabolism.', 'minerals', '/images/minerals/1725024560209.webp'),
	(23, 'Cu', 'Copper', '<table>   <tr>     <th>Age</th>     <th>Male</th>     <th>Female</th>     <th>Pregnancy</th>     <th>Lactation</th>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>Birth to 6 months*</td>     <td>200 mcg</td>     <td>200 mcg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>7–12 months*</td>     <td>220 mcg</td>     <td>220 mcg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>1–3 years</td>     <td>340 mcg</td>     <td>340 mcg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>4–8 years</td>     <td>440 mcg</td>     <td>440 mcg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>9–13 years</td>     <td>700 mcg</td>     <td>700 mcg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>14–18 years</td>     <td>890 mcg</td>     <td>890 mcg</td>     <td>1,000 mcg</td>     <td>1,300 mcg</td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>19+ years</td>     <td>900 mcg</td>     <td>900 mcg</td>     <td>1,000 mcg</td>     <td>1,300 mcg</td>   </tr> </table>', 'Copper is an essential trace mineral that plays a vital role in the proper functioning of the human body. While it may not be as well-known as some of its counterparts, copper is a versatile nutrient that contributes to a wide range of physiological processes, from the formation of red blood cells to the maintenance of healthy skin and hair.', 'minerals', '/images/minerals/1725024595268.webp'),
	(24, 'I', 'Iodine', '<table>   <tr>     <th>Age</th>     <th>Male</th>     <th>Female</th>     <th>Pregnancy</th>     <th>Lactation</th>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>Birth to 6 months</td>     <td>110 mcg*</td>     <td>110 mcg*</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>7–12 months</td>     <td>130 mcg*</td>     <td>130 mcg*</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>1–3 years</td>     <td>90 mcg</td>     <td>90 mcg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>4–8 years</td>     <td>90 mcg</td>     <td>90 mcg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>9–13 years</td>     <td>120 mcg</td>     <td>120 mcg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>14–18 years</td>     <td>150 mcg</td>     <td>150 mcg</td>     <td>220 mcg</td>     <td>290 mcg</td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>19+ years</td>     <td>150 mcg</td>     <td>150 mcg</td>     <td>220 mcg</td>     <td>290 mcg</td>   </tr> </table>', 'Iodine is an essential trace mineral that plays a crucial role in the proper functioning of the thyroid gland, a small but mighty endocrine organ located in the neck. While it may not be as well-known as some of its counterparts, iodine is a vital nutrient that contributes to the regulation of metabolism, energy production, and overall bodily function.', 'minerals', '/images/minerals/1725024618384.webp'),
	(25, 'F', 'Fluoride', '<table>   <tr>     <th>Age</th>     <th>Male</th>     <th>Female</th>     <th>Pregnancy</th>     <th>Lactation</th>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>Birth to 6 months</td>     <td>0.01 mg</td>     <td>0.01 mg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>7–12 months</td>     <td>0.5 mg</td>     <td>0.5 mg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>1–3 years</td>     <td>0.7 mg</td>     <td>0.7 mg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>4–8 years</td>     <td>1 mg</td>     <td>1 mg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>9–13 years</td>     <td>2 mg</td>     <td>2 mg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>14–18 years</td>     <td>3 mg</td>     <td>3 mg</td>     <td>3 mg</td>     <td>3 mg</td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>19+ years</td>     <td>4 mg</td>     <td>3 mg</td>     <td>3 mg</td>     <td>3 mg</td>   </tr> </table>', 'Fluoride is a mineral that has long been recognized for its crucial role in maintaining the health of our teeth and gums. While it may not be as widely known for its broader health benefits, fluoride is a versatile compound that contributes to the overall well-being of the human body.', 'minerals', '/images/minerals/1725024717835.webp'),
	(26, 'Mo', 'Molybdenum', '<table>   <tr>     <th>Age</th>     <th>Male</th>     <th>Female</th>     <th>Pregnancy</th>     <th>Lactation</th>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>Birth to 6 months</td>     <td>2 mcg*</td>     <td>2 mcg*</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>7–12 months</td>     <td>3 mcg*</td>     <td>3 mcg*</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>1–3 years</td>     <td>17 mcg</td>     <td>17 mcg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>4–8 years</td>     <td>22 mcg</td>     <td>22 mcg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>9–13 years</td>     <td>34 mcg</td>     <td>34 mcg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>14–18 years</td>     <td>43 mcg</td>     <td>43 mcg</td>     <td>50 mcg</td>     <td>50 mcg</td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>19+ years</td>     <td>45 mcg</td>     <td>45 mcg</td>     <td>50 mcg</td>     <td>50 mcg</td>   </tr> </table>', 'Molybdenum is a trace mineral that, despite its relatively low profile, plays a crucial role in the proper functioning of the human body. While it may not be as well-known as some of its more prominent counterparts, molybdenum is a versatile nutrient that contributes to a wide range of physiological processes, from the metabolism of proteins to the detoxification of harmful compounds.', 'minerals', '/images/minerals/1725024741140.webp'),
	(27, 'Ca', 'Calcium', '<table>   <tr>     <th>Age</th>     <th>Male</th>     <th>Female</th>     <th>Pregnant</th>     <th>Lactating</th>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>0–6 months*</td>     <td>200 mg</td>     <td>200 mg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>7–12 months*</td>     <td>260 mg</td>     <td>260 mg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>1–3 years</td>     <td>700 mg</td>     <td>700 mg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>4–8 years</td>     <td>1,000 mg</td>     <td>1,000 mg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>9–13 years</td>     <td>1,300 mg</td>     <td>1,300 mg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>14–18 years</td>     <td>1,300 mg</td>     <td>1,300 mg</td>     <td>1,300 mg</td>     <td>1,300 mg</td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>19–50 years</td>     <td>1,000 mg</td>     <td>1,000 mg</td>     <td>1,000 mg</td>     <td>1,000 mg</td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>51–70 years</td>     <td>1,000 mg</td>     <td>1,200 mg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td>>70+ years</td>     <td>1,200 mg</td>     <td>1,200 mg</td>     <td></td>     <td></td>   </tr> </table>', 'Calcium is a remarkable mineral that plays a crucial role in various aspects of human health. As an essential nutrient, it is primarily known for its importance in the development and maintenance of strong, healthy bones and teeth. However, its functions extend far beyond just bone health.', 'minerals', '/images/minerals/1725024276246.webp'),
	(28, 'Mg', 'Magnesium', '   <h2>Recommended Daily Allowance (RDA) for Magnesium by Age and Sex</h2>\n    <p>The following table shows the recommended daily allowance (RDA) for magnesium intake by age and sex, according to the ODSTrusted Source.</p>\n    <table>\n        <thead>\n            <tr>\n                <th>Age</th>\n                <th>Male</th>\n                <th>Female</th>\n            </tr>\n        </thead>\n        <tbody>\n            <tr>\n                <td>1–3 years</td>\n                <td>80 mg</td>\n                <td>80 mg</td>\n            </tr>\n            <tr>\n                <td>4–8 years</td>\n                <td>130 mg</td>\n                <td>130 mg</td>\n            </tr>\n            <tr>\n                <td>9–13 years</td>\n                <td>240 mg</td>\n                <td>240 mg</td>\n            </tr>\n            <tr>\n                <td>14–18 years</td>\n                <td>410 mg</td>\n                <td>360 mg</td>\n            </tr>\n            <tr>\n                <td>19–30 years</td>\n                <td>400 mg</td>\n                <td>310 mg</td>\n            </tr>\n            <tr>\n                <td>31–50 years</td>\n                <td>420 mg</td>\n                <td>320 mg</td>\n            </tr>\n            <tr>\n                <td>51+ years</td>\n                <td>420 mg</td>\n                <td>320 mg</td>\n            </tr>\n        </tbody>\n    </table>\n    <p>People should increase their magnesium intake by around 40 mg per day during pregnancy.</p>\n    <p>Experts base the adequate intake for babies under 1 year old on the amounts found in breastmilk.</p>', 'Magnesium plays a role in over 300 enzyme reactions in the human body. Magnesium functions include helping with muscle and nerve function, regulating blood pressure, and supporting the immune system.', 'minerals', '/images/minerals/magnesium.webp');
